ETYMOLOGY: For Dashe (ca. 1910–1980, fig. 7), also known as Quioshash, a hero of the Matses people. Dashe grew up during the rubber boom, when mercenaries were sent to Matses territory to exterminate the indigenous inhabitants. Dashe grew up fleeing from attackers who killed his kinsmen and carried off women and children to be prostituted or sold as slaves. After he had grown to manhood, Dashe rallied the Matses to fight back, leading multiple successful raids on rubber camps and settlements, eventually expelling all outsiders (
Jiménez Huanán et al., 2014
). Without his courage and military cunning the Matses would no longer exist as an intact culture with legally recognized title to their tribal land.
